<paragraph id="8BDA36DDFFB0E951FF76FA2CA74DF923" blockId="1.[151,1436,1491,1791]" pageId="1" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis id="B911EACFFFB0E951FF76FA2CA45DFA5E" bold="true" box="[151,360,1491,1514]" pageId="1" pageNumber="436">Generic diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body small and slender. Vertex convex, eyes vertically lengthened, 
<number id="3DAD24FAFFB0E951FBA5FA2CA165FA5E" box="[1092,1104,1491,1514]" pageId="1" pageNumber="436" value="5.0">5</number>
th joint of maxillary palpi long and widened apically. Pronotum transverse. Tegmen slightly extending to apex of wings, rather convex and slightly sclerotized, lacking a stridulatory file, covered with fine pubescence, venation similar in both sexes. Fore tibia without tympana; hind tibia with three pairs of dorsal spurs and five apical spurs, of which two internal and three external spurs. Male genitalia: epiphallus present with lateral lobes, which are finely toothed along internal margins; endophallus developed. Ovipositor long, curved upwards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6556FFB0E951FF26F95CA792F969" pageId="1" pageNumber="436" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDA36DDFFB0E951FF26F95CA792F969" blockId="1.[151,1436,1491,1791]" pageId="1" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis id="B911EACFFFB0E951FF26F95CA400F90E" bold="true" box="[199,309,1699,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="436">Remarks.</emphasis>
